# Contribution Guidelines

## Code Standards
1. Follow consistent formatting and style
2. Document all public APIs and interfaces
3. Write clear commit messages

## Documentation Contributions
1. Follow the established directory structure
2. Update relevant documentation when making code changes
3. Use Markdown for all documentation files
4. Include examples for complex features
5. Test all code samples before submitting

## Review Process
1. Documentation is clear and follows guidelines
2. Code examples are working and up-to-date
3. Cross-references are valid
4. No sensitive information is included

## Pull Request Guidelines
1. Reference related issues
2. Include a clear description of changes
3. Update documentation as needed
4. Add tests for new features
5. Ensure all checks pass
